## Business Problem

A manufacturing company produces two products: Product A and Product B.

Each product requires machine hours and labor hours for production.
The company has limited resources and wants to determine the optimal
production quantities to maximize profit.
## Business Data

Profit per unit:

Product A = ₹40  
Product B = ₹30  

Resource availability:

Machine hours available = 100  
Labor hours available = 80  

Resource requirement per product:

Product A:
Machine hours = 2
Labor hours = 1

Product B:
Machine hours = 1
Labor hours = 1
## Mathematical Formulation

Let:

x = units of Product A  
y = units of Product B  

Objective Function:

Maximize

Z = 40x + 30y

Constraints:

2x + y ≤ 100  (Machine hours)

x + y ≤ 80    (Labor hours)
x ≥ 0 , y ≥ 0

## In Code Cells
import pulp
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
model = pulp.LpProblem("Product_Mix_Optimization", pulp.LpMaximize)
x = pulp.LpVariable('Product_A', lowBound=0)
y = pulp.LpVariable('Product_B', lowBound=0)
model += 40*x + 30*y
model += 2*x + y <= 100
model += x + y <= 80
model.solve()
print("Status:", pulp.LpStatus[model.status])
print("Product A:", pulp.value(x))
print("Product B:", pulp.value(y))
print("Maximum Profit:", pulp.value(model.objective))
products = ["Product A","Product B"]
values = [pulp.value(x), pulp.value(y)]

plt.bar(products, values)
plt.title("Optimal Production Plan")
plt.ylabel("Units Produced")
plt.show()


